The paper proposes a method for improving deep reinforcement learning with sparse rewards, which is a common problem in robotics and navigation tasks. The method involves using predictive coding to shape the reward signal, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.RO (Robotics). Additionally, the paper applies the method to robotic manipulation and navigation tasks, which suggests that cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) are also likely sub-categories.
